Doesn't give notifications no matter what settings you change. Results in you missing announcements, assignments, and pop-quizzes. Also doesn't allow for multiple canvas accounts. I attend multiple community colleges because of scheduling restrictions and I am forced to log in to each school's canvas every time. It is a painfully slow process and makes the experience very annoying for me. Seamless transitioning to another account (i.e. saving the account) or having the ability to log into multiple accounts at once and have all of your courses available to you at the same time would greatly improve the experience. Push notifications would also be more useful than an email, as the email on phones don't sync very often and results in not receiving notifications until another device is used. Many of the other features of this app are great, but these lacking areas could be improved upon and would make it a much more useful tool.

On the virtual days I have to check in to my classes for attendance via a Canvas quiz. When I submit the quiz through the app, it *always* says it's submitted successfully. I have never missed a single attendance quiz, however, I have received SIX absences this year for failing to submit attendance quizzes. Well, the Canvas app hasn't actually been submitting the quizzes. Turns out when the app says the quiz was submitted successfully, it isn't always right. Sometimes when I submit a quiz through the app, and then check on the Canvas website, it says it wasn't actually submitted! When I figured out that's what was happening with those 6 absences, I now always check the website to make sure the quiz was submitted. Sometimes I even have to re-submit it 5+ times on the app before it'll actually go through!! I have explained this to my teachers. Unbelievably, they have told me that they will not correct the six absences that were entirely caused by incompetent software developers. The team of chimpanzees behind this app have put me ONE ABSENCE AWAY FROM DETENTION. Not because I did anything wrong. I trusted that this app would do what it was supposed to do. The app failed, and failed hard. I rest my case.

I have been using canvas for over 3 years now. I use it now more than ever, since I am doing virtual classes. I do have a suggestion: I recommend adding an audio/video call option, since I have to sign in to Zoom for all 5 of my daily video calls. It would just be nice to be able to click something and go straight to my classes. It could be easier for students in my district, since we have to have an authorized account for our calls. If we had calls on Canvas, no students would have to sign in every time and the teachers would know which student it is since most of us are signed in by name. It may not be possible to add that, but if there is, I would highly recommend it. Other than that, It's pretty ok. It lags a lot, especially on PC, and it's really a pain when I misspell something even when spelling doesn't count for our grade. Luckily, my teachers go in and look through our assignments and grade them even after they were "graded" by Canvas. I also would like to suggest adding a "go in and double-check" feature, because I often miss-click an answer and get it wrong. If these features are added and the problems are fixed, I might rate it 5 stars, depending on how good it is.

I use this app to keep track of my university work as well as to submit some worksheets. It's mostly helpful, yeah, but I'm giving it only 3 stars as it's significantly jeopardized me with how it doesn't seem to post EVERYTHING I need to keep in mind. Maintaining a manually-written to-do list is one thing, but people can forget to add things to that list. People will be swamped with work and reviewing the week before finals only to be scared out of their seats because it turns out they forget to work on and submit THREE worksheets that only showed up in the calendar/online to-do list on the actual day it was due. I checked the due date religiously on the app and it wasn't there. And now that I've checked the Canvas WEBSITE it turns out the activity was around for already a WEEK and I never knew about it, because the calendar/to-do list of the app doesn't show everything. As someone who uses the computer primarily for typing papers or taking tests while relying on the tablet for everything else, this is just terrible. This app has genuinely jeopardized me and worn thin on my patience.

The app is extremely easy to learn how to use. I have being using this app for around two weeks. It has been a really great experience, also the way how you communicate with teachers and turn in your assignments. It even gives you the opportunity to repeat your quizzes or multiple choice assignments, just to make sure that you really learned from every unit. It hasn't glitch the app till now, runs fast and great quality. 10 out of 10.

Does everything essential, but misses some fringe marks. This app is the go-to choice for using canvas on mobile. Animations are smooth, things are well placed, and the only overall UX detractor is lack of a dark mode. That said, some small features available on the web app are not present in this version. Future enrollments, for example, are not visible under "All Courses." A student might mistake this oversight as failure to enroll on their part and cause unnecessary panic.
